Rating: 3
I quite liked it, though I made some adjustments to allow for food allergies and such in my house. So, here's my adjustment, and I'll surely try some other suggestions from previous reviewers the next time, like the addition of mustard (I'm sure this recipe is very good as is, too). Instead of milk in the sauce I used unsweetened soymilk, which worked great. For the cheese, I used yogurt cheese. To make up for the lack of sharpness in the cheese, I also added a bunch of paprika for color and a smoky kick (yum). I added two grated carrots (because I love grated carrot with cauliflower), and also threw in two chicken thighs, cubed and sauteed. With the addition of the chicken, it made a great one-dish dinner. Didn't have saltines (or horseradish for that matter) so I used large bread crumbs (similar to panko, which I'd have used if I'd had any in the house). So yes, I know, this isn't really totally the same as the original recipe, but basically I had this cauliflower staring at me from the fridge, and needed inspiration. I'll venture to say that the original is a tasty starting place that allows for easy improvisation, which is always a plus!

